 ('1', '21', '6', '1', 'en_us', 'Draft 1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Vim: A Love Story\",\"slug\":\"vim-a-love-story\",\"postDate\":null,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"4\":\"<p>I won\'t lie. The first time I found myself inside of vim I&nbsp;was, as a kind way to put it, confused. Vim is a frustratingly confusing editor, but it is also an extremely powerful and lightweight editor that has the power to change the way you write software.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>A Little History<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Vim is a clone of vi, an old Unix based editor that is still around today. It\'s more than likely that vi is living on the system you\'re using right now. Wether it\'s a laptop, workstation, or smartphone, if you can access you system\'s terminal, you can access vi. So why is vi so ubiquitous?&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"3\":\"Vim: A Love Story\"}}', '2016-05-29 22:52:06', '2016-05-29 23:03:04', '2c168756-129a-406d-8a81-75b5e9d50968');



